		<td><b>Famicom disk system strap slipping and jamming</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I received from my brother in law in Japan a while ago a broken Famicom disk system.  After opening it, the problem was the usual one: a melted strap.
<br />
<br />I was able to find in Akihabara a new strap, followed the instruction from a website on the net (I think it was this <a href="http://www.pinkgodzillagames.com/retro_reviews/simply_ness_guide_to_famicom_d.php" class="postlink">one</a>) and it seemed to work. Games were booting and everything.  The only problem is that once in a while, the strap start to slip and jam. So you have to re-open the unit and put back the strap in place.
<br />
<br />Does anybody had this issue before?  I'm not sure if I missed something in the procedure or the strap could be the issue.

		

